/* ============================================================================
   culture_dashboard/data.js  —  OFFLINE FALLBACK SNAPSHOT (not the source of truth)
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   The Culture Dashboard is wired to read the SAME data as the existing live
   tracker. See culture_dashboard/app.js -> loadData()/normalizeData(). At
   runtime the board loads, in priority order:

     1. live_tracker.html  -> the <script id="data" type="application/json"> blob
        that the tracker itself parses. This is the tracker's actual runtime
        data source, so the board can never drift from the tracker.
     2. sessions.json      -> a standalone file in the repo that is currently
        byte-for-byte deep-equal to that inline tracker blob.
     3. THIS FILE          -> a static design-time snapshot, used ONLY when both
        fetches above fail (e.g. the page is opened from file:// where browsers
        block fetch). It keeps the board populated offline.

   WHY A TRANSFORM IS NEEDED (format differences between the two sources)
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   The tracker data (sessions.json / inline blob) and the dashboard's original
   design snapshot (this file) share the same shape — { tracks, cols, cards } —
   but the dashboard adds two card fields the tracker does NOT have:

       day1Built : boolean   // drives the green "Built at Camp" flag, the
                             //   charcoal "Shipped · Culture Camp Day 1" drawer
                             //   banner, and the feature-KPI "teachable moments"
       builtAt   : string    // e.g. "Culture Camp · Day 1"

   app.js -> normalizeCard() bridges that gap. If a card already carries a
   boolean `day1Built` (this snapshot does), it is used as-is. Otherwise it is
   DERIVED from the live tracker data with the rule:

       day1Built = (view === "student" && col === "Day 1" && status === "Built")

   i.e. a Day-1 student session that the tracker marks Built earns the
   "built at camp" treatment. Because it keys off the tracker's live `status`,
   the dashboard's celebratory flags stay honest and move with the tracker.
   Every tracker card already contains the 8 resource keys the drawer reads
   (Source status, Student-facing lesson, Rehearsal card, Coaching look-for,
   ...), so the resource path renders correctly with no extra mapping.

   TO FULLY UNIFY (single source of truth, zero drift) — future work:
   ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Today the tracker embeds its data INLINE and only *happens* to match
   sessions.json. To make them truly inseparable, pick ONE of:
     (a) Make the tracker fetch sessions.json instead of inlining the blob, so
         both views read the one file. (Touches live_tracker.html — intentionally
         NOT done here per the "do not touch the tracker" constraint.)
     (b) Add real `day1Built` / `builtAt` fields to sessions.json (and the
         tracker blob) so the dashboard consumes them directly and the derive
         rule above becomes a no-op. Confirm the field semantics with the data
         owner before restructuring.
     (c) Add a tiny build/CI step that regenerates sessions.json from the
         tracker's inline blob (or vice-versa) on every change, so the two
         copies can never diverge. Then delete this fallback file.
   Until one of those lands, keep this file as the offline fallback only.
   ============================================================================ */

